h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create a page in a personal space containing two HTML macros:
{code}
<div class="test-datepicker"></div>
{code}
AND 
{code}<script>
AJS.toInit(function() {
	AJS.$(".test-datepicker").datepicker({
		inline: true
		, showButtonPanel: true
	});
  });
</script>
{code}
# Save the page - you will see the month/year bar is stretched:
!datepicker.png!
# Create the same page in another space (not a personal space) and you will see the datepicker displays correctly

h3. Cause
This is caused by the personal-info-sidebar in the personal space - it floats to the right, and because of this other elements can be distorted (there is a "Clearfix" on certain datepicker elements generated by the JavaScript)

h3. Workaround
# Go to Space Admin for the personal space
# Edit the Stylesheet
# Enter this CSS to hide some datepicker elements:
{code}
.ui-datepicker-inline .ui-helper-clearfix::after,
.ui-datepicker-inline::after { 
    display: none;
}

.ui-datepicker-inline .ui-datepicker-buttonpane { oveflow: hidden; }
{code}
# Refresh the page and you will see it displays correctly

