Resulting in half the content not being visible.

Affects: 5.0-CDOG-2267

h4. Steps to Reproduce
# Add the following in your Site Welcome Message:
{code}
{info}
this is an info text
{info}
{code} 
!siteWelcomeMsgEdit.png!
# Save it, and it'll look like this:
!siteWelcomeMsg.png!
# Visit the dashboard, it'll be displayed like this:
!infoMacro_onDashboard.png!
# Now create/edit a Page and add the same macro, it'll be displayed like this (*this is the expected and correct result/look*):
!infoMacro_onPage.png!

h4. Possible cause
It seems that the CSS of the info macro styling {{information-plugin-styles.css}} that comes from:
{code}
2.0.8/_/download/batch/confluence.extra.information:information-plugin-styles/confluence.extra.information:information-plugin-styles.css
{code} 
is not loaded/included when loading the dashboard. Hence the style or CSS of the macro is missing.

h4. Workaround
Add the missing style/CSS manually in Confluence Admin >> Stylesheet. 

For the example above, this is the missing one that should get the background colour right:
{code}
.infoMessage, .infoMacro {
    border-color: #69c;
    background-color: #d8e4f1;
}
{code}

